(21,12,'page_detail','Undergraduate Study','<p><strong>Fresh Students Admissions</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Thank you for your interest in applying for admission to Jakarta Global University!</p>\r\n\r\n<p>If you are a current high school student, or in matriculation colleges, or attending pre-university courses in other colleges, and you have not attended college since graduating from high school, complete the undergraduate application.&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><u>Active Email Address</u></p>\r\n\r\n<p>An active email address is required on the application form in order to contact you during the application process. After enrolment however, the University will provide all students with an JGU email for any internal university correspondences.</p>\r\n','undergraduate-study',NULL,1,NULL,NULL,'','','','','2023-11-08 16:10:31',NULL,NULL,NULL,1),
(22,12,'page_detail','Postgraduate Study','<p>Jakarta Global University offers graduate programs and faculty focused on learner-centred, discovery-driven and globally-engaged education.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Post-graduate | Master in Electrical Engineering Programs</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n','postgraduate-study',NULL,1,NULL,NULL,'','','','','2023-11-08 16:10:31',NULL,NULL,NULL,1),
(23,13,'page_detail','Continuing & Extended Education Centre (CEdEC)','<p>The Continuing &amp; Extended Education Centre (CEdEC) was established with the aim to excel at providing continuing education in tandem with society&#39;s current needs</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Promoting lifelong education, CEdEC offers Language &amp; Communication Courses, Technology &amp; Skills Courses,&nbsp;Creative media courses, People Management &amp; Leadership Courses, Business &amp; Managerial Skills Courses.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>CEdEC strives to meet community demands and is able to customize its courses to individual or corporate needs.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>LONGLIFE EDUCATION</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>JGU SHORT COURSE</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Language &amp; Communication Courses,&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>Technology &amp; Skills Courses,&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>Creative media courses,&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>People Management &amp; Leadership Courses,&nbsp;</li>\r\n	<li>Business &amp; Managerial Skills Courses,&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>SCHOOL HOLIDAY PROGRAM</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Sciences and Technology</li>\r\n	<li>Creative arts</li>\r\n	<li>Soft skill training courses</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>LANGUAGE &amp; COMMUNICATION COURSES&nbsp;</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Communicative English</li>\r\n	<li>Communicative Mandarin (Basic to Advanced)</li>\r\n	<li>Communicative Mandarin (Basic to Advanced)</li>\r\n	<li>English for Occupational Enhancement</li>\r\n	<li>Professional certification in Grammar</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>TECHNOLOGY &amp; SKILLS COURSES</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Arduino Essential Training</li>\r\n	<li>Basic Electrical &amp; Electronic for Non-Electrical Personel</li>\r\n	<li>Computer Forensic</li>\r\n	<li>Solid Work for Technical Drawing</li>\r\n	<li>Web Programming for Beginners</li>\r\n	<li>Microsoft Office Word (Basic to Advanced)</li>\r\n	<li>Microsoft Office Excel (Basic to Advanced)</li>\r\n	<li>Microsoft Office Power Point (Basic to Advanced)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>CREATIVE MEDIA COURSES</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Adobe Illustrator : Fundamentals&nbsp;of Graphic Illustrations for Beginner Learner</li>\r\n	<li>Animation short course</li>\r\n	<li>Adobe Photoshop</li>\r\n	<li>3D Design : Mastering&nbsp;the Fundamental of 3D Modeling by Using Blender 3D</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>PEOPLE MANAGEMENT &amp; LEADERSHIP</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Thinking Skills</li>\r\n	<li>Communication Skills</li>\r\n	<li>Management Skills</li>\r\n	<li>Teamwork Skills</li>\r\n	<li>Leadership Skills</li>\r\n	<li>Entrepreneurship Skills</li>\r\n	<li>Wellness Management</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>BUSINESS &amp; MANAGERIAL&nbsp;SKILLS COURSES</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Time Management</li>\r\n	<li>Leadership &amp; Teambuilding Workshop</li>\r\n	<li>Training Need Analysis (TNA)</li>\r\n	<li>Cross Cultural Awareness</li>\r\n	<li>Critical &amp; Creative Thinking</li>\r\n	<li>Writing Skills</li>\r\n	<li>Professional Image - Grooming &amp; Etiquette</li>\r\n	<li>Social Media Marketing</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>SCHOOL HOLIDAY PROGRAMME</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Sciences and Technology</li>\r\n	<li>Creative arts</li>\r\n	<li>Soft skill training courses</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>INDUSTRY AND CORPORATE TRAINING</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Foreign Languages</li>\r\n	<li>Technical skill</li>\r\n	<li>Thinking Skills</li>\r\n	<li>Communication Skills</li>\r\n	<li>Management Skills</li>\r\n	<li>Teamwork Skills</li>\r\n	<li>Leadership Skills</li>\r\n	<li>Entrepreneurship Skills</li>\r\n	<li>Wellness Management</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Contact:&nbsp;<br />\r\nRevita Desi Hertin +6283802434392<br />\r\nAli Ridho +62 877-8539-6990<br />\r\nMail cedec@jgu.ac.id</p>\r\n','cedec',NULL,1,'cedec-banner_20210331070640.jpg',NULL,'','','','','2023-11-08 16:10:31',NULL,NULL,NULL,1),
(24,14,'page_detail','Why JGU','<p>Welcome to JGU<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\nWelcome to JGU, your global university of choice.&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\nWe are committed to transforming lives, enriching future.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\nTake advantage of the unique opportunities we offer.&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>&nbsp;<br />\r\nTOWARDS BEING GLOBAL CITIZENS AT JGU<br />\r\n________________________________________</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Jakarta Global University is a global university that emphasizes the success of its graduates, both in academic excellence and soft skills in order to produce a holistic, balance and well-rounded graduate.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\nThe moment you step into the JGU campus; you will experience the dynamic cultural diversity that is felt all around. Our students bring life into the overall vibrancy on site, with their combination of personalities and lifestyles. Their different racial or academic backgrounds and experiences, add unique features of the university, where individual growth and communication are leveraged.&nbsp;<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\nMOBILITY<br />\r\nOur international students also add to this existing cultural diversity and you can anticipate the interesting campus life activities, where cultures and customs collide. Our students are given opportunities to gain international exposure while they study here. Similarly, international students planning for shorter period of time can also come to experience the global mobility program we offer.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\nThe Global Mobility Program (GMP), Global Leadership Program (GLP) and Global Internship Program (GIP) allow students to empower their global experience with JGU university partners around the world such as the Malaysia, Turkey, Ireland, Japan, China, Taiwan and more as their hub for knowledge.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\nThe participation of students in these programs strengthens their appreciation for social and cultural uniqueness, information sharing and skills, learning and teaching systems, collaborative networks, new partners, community service and as a &#39;small ambassador&#39; of the State.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>&nbsp;<br />\r\nSTUDENT SUPPORT</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;In JGU, the local and international student supports all international students and activities such as:<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Facilitates new students during registration<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Assists international students to get adjusted in the new environment<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Organizes activities that celebrate diversity and cultures across countries<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Supports students&rsquo; needs around the campus&nbsp;<br />\r\n&bull;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;Disseminates relevant information where necessary<br />\r\nThere is a place for everyone at JGU, where education is offered through an entry system that facilitates admission from all walks of life, locally and internationally. We are committed towards providing the journey that will help to transform lives and enriching the future for all.<br />\r\n&nbsp;<br />\r\nWe look forward to having you at JGU!<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n','why-jgu',NULL,1,NULL,NULL,'','','','','2023-11-08 16:10:31',NULL,NULL,NULL,1),
(25,14,'page_detail','Our Location','<p><strong>Kampus C (Utama)</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Grand Depok City, Jl. Boulevard Raya No. 2, Tirtajaya, Sukmajaya, Kota Depok.</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p><strong>Kampus A</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Jl. Jatiwaringin Raya No. 278 Pondok Gede 17411, Jakarta</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p><strong>Kampus B</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Jl. H. Saimun, Cibuntu Kec. Cibitung Kab. Bekasi, Jawa Barat</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<p><iframe height=\"400\" src=\"https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d3964.8076375201854!2d106.82527151471783!3d-6.418757595355911!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x2e69eb97981e953d%3A0x7040f2673277d58f!2sKampus%20Jakarta%20Global%20University!5e0!3m2!1sen!2sid!4v1624009858181!5m2!1sen!2sid\" style=\"border:0;\" width=\"100%\"></iframe></p>\r\n','our-location',NULL,1,NULL,NULL,'','','','','2023-11-08 16:10:31',NULL,NULL,NULL,1),
(26,14,'page_detail','Library & Resource Centre','<h2>JGU LIBRARY AND RESOURCE CENTER</h2>\r\n\r\n<h3><br />\r\nGeneral Rules and Regulations</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Library users must present their library membership card clearly when entering the Library. Library membership card is not transferable.</li>\r\n	<li>Smoking, consumption of food and drink, is not permitted in the Library.</li>\r\n	<li>No bags, umbrellas, parcels, etc. except files and books may be brought to the library. Adequate storage facilities have been provided at the entrance of the Library. The library is not responsible for the loss or misplacement of personal items in its premises.</li>\r\n	<li>Visitors must maintain order in the library.</li>\r\n	<li>The phone is limited to silent mode only.</li>\r\n	<li>Users should dress modestly and behave in a good manner in the Library.</li>\r\n	<li>Users must keep the library clean.</li>\r\n	<li>Pets are not allowed in the Library.</li>\r\n	<li>Seat reservations are not permitted. Library staff has the right to pick up items left on the table within a specified time period.</li>\r\n	<li>Users are not allowed to move library furniture and equipment from their original place.</li>\r\n	<li>Library staff have the right to ask a user to leave the library if he or she is found to have violated any of the Library regulations.</li>\r\n	<li>The library staff on duty is entitled to checkbooks, archives, and other materials removed from the library.</li>\r\n	<li>Disciplinary action will be taken against library users found with material from the library collection, without proper permission.</li>\r\n	<li>The Chief Librarian is authorized to withhold the Library facilities for any violation of this rule.</li>\r\n	<li>The Head Librarian may amend the Library Rules and Regulations if necessary.</li>\r\n	<li>All library members must comply with the rules and regulations.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2>Library Locker</h2>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Lockers are open to all users of the Jakarta Global University Library.</li>\r\n	<li>Users who want to borrow lockers are required to report to the officer in advance</li>\r\n	<li>Maximum usage from 8.00 to 22.00. If the user exceeds that, the library is allowed to open and eject items.</li>\r\n	<li>Placing posters or other items in lockers is not permitted.</li>\r\n	<li>Lockers must be emptied in a clean condition.</li>\r\n	<li>The library is not responsible for any loss or damage to materials stored in lockers.</li>\r\n	<li>For further information relating to lockers should be submitted to the clerk at the library counter.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2>Collection Loan</h2>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Students show active student cards or temporary student cards, while lecturers show employee cards or library cards to officers.</li>\r\n	<li>Invalid student card / cannot be loaned to others.</li>\r\n	<li>Students who have obtained a Library Free Certificate (SKBP), cannot borrow books from the library including for photocopying.</li>\r\n	<li>Reference Books (Books, Dictionaries, Encyclopedias, Magazines, Journals, Final Projects, Thesis) can only be read on the spot.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2>Loan Allocation</h2>\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>JGU Undergraduate Student\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Maximum loan: 4 different titles.</li>\r\n		<li>Maximum loan term: 1 week (without extension).</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>JGU Masters Program Students\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Maximum loan: 5 different titles.</li>\r\n		<li>Maximum loan term: 2 weeks (no extension).</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>Lecturers and Education Personnel\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Maximum loan: 6 different titles.</li>\r\n		<li>Maximum loan term: 3 months (without extension).</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>Alumni and Non-JGU: Borrow from the library only\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Limited collections and favorites: 1 week loan period.</li>\r\n		<li>CD Book Collection: Loan period of 2 days.</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h2>Sanctions</h2>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Late repatriation is subject to a fine of Rp. 3000, - / day.</li>\r\n	<li>Deletion / destruction of books must be replaced with the same book, if the same book is not available, the borrower replaces the book with a relatively equal price and the contents are determined by the Head of the Library Service.</li>\r\n	<li>Locker key returns during service opening hours, after service hours, are subject to a fine of Rp. 5,000 / day.</li>\r\n	<li>Removing the locker key is subject to a fine of Rp. 25,000.</li>\r\n	<li>Visitors / library users who do not meet the requirements can be given academic sanctions and revocation of membership.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2>Additional Rules</h2>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Visitors / library users must actively participate in complying with the rules that have been set and maintaining order, cleanliness / tidiness of the environment.</li>\r\n	<li>Books that have been read leave on the table or in the space provided.</li>\r\n	<li>Visitors must leave the library, including the public reading room, after the library services are closed.</li>\r\n	<li>Students who need a Library Free Certificate (SKBP) can contact the general circulation section, provided that they no longer have borrowed books or lockers in the library.</li>\r\n	<li>Students who have passed are required to submit a Final Project in the form of:\r\n	<ul>\r\n		<li>Thesis Report (3 pieces)</li>\r\n		<li>Softcopy of thesis report (on CD as much as 1 piece)</li>\r\n		<li>Job Training Report (3 pieces)</li>\r\n		<li>Miscellaneous (Tools, A3 Posters, etc.)</li>\r\n	</ul>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>Things that are not included in this regulation will be determined later.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2>Membership</h2>\r\n\r\n<h3>Requirements</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Library members are all JGU Academic Civitas.</li>\r\n	<li>The student shows an active KTM, the lecturer shows an employee card.</li>\r\n	<li>There are two types of library cards available at the JGU library, namely printed cards and online membership cards</li>\r\n	<li>The membership period is valid as long as you are active as a JGU student.</li>\r\n	<li>Visitors from outside the JGU campus, can take advantage of library services with the following conditions: show a valid identity card and be charged a fee of Rp. 10,000,- / visit</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2>Code of Conduct</h2>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Member card (printed/online) must be brought every time you visit</li>\r\n	<li>Membership cards cannot be loaned to other people</li>\r\n	<li>If the membership card is lost, it is obligatory to make a certificate of loss and a letter of agreement regulated by the library.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2>Catalog and Classification System / Documentation System</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Library collections are cataloged, classified and organized according to international standards. The JGU Library and Resource Center used AACR2 (Anglo American Cataloging Rules 2) to catalog all materials and DDC (Dewey Decimal Classification) LCC (Library of Congress Classification) and National Library Medicine (NLM for medical books) to develop number calls. As for the subject headings, the library uses LCSH (Library of Congress Subject Headings) as a reference.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Facilities and Services</h2>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Borrow/Return/Update/Reserve books through computerized library system</li>\r\n	<li>Reference Materials - Books, Monographs and Multimedia</li>\r\n	<li>Student Project/Thesis online.</li>\r\n	<li>Terminal OPAC (Online Public Access Catalog)</li>\r\n	<li>Open Reading Area</li>\r\n	<li>Magazines and periodicals</li>\r\n	<li>Mainstream Newspaper</li>\r\n	<li>Reference Collection</li>\r\n	<li>Medical Collection</li>\r\n	<li>Wireless Broadband Facility</li>\r\n	<li>Special Area for Laptop Users</li>\r\n	<li>Education &amp; Entertainment Space</li>\r\n	<li>Discussion Room</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2>Discussion Room Borrowing</h2>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Borrowing discussion room for students showing the active KTM or temporary KTM, while the lecturer shows the employee card or library card to the librarian</li>\r\n	<li>Fill out the Consultation Room Loan Form</li>\r\n	<li>Consultation room loan is done at least 1 hour before using the room.</li>\r\n	<li>The room can only be used during library service hours.</li>\r\n	<li>Detention of membership card/KTM by officers as long as the room is still used by visitors.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2>Collection</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>The Jakarta Global University Library has many types of collections, ranging from Fiction to Science Materials, from printed materials to digital collections such as CD-ROMs, CDs, VCDs and DVDs. The JGU library also collects daily serial publications such as newspapers as well as monthly serials such as magazines.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><br />\r\nLIST OF BOOK COLLECTIONS IN JAKARTA GLOBAL UNIVERSITY LIBRARY</p>\r\n\r\n<table border=\"1\" cellspacing=\"0\" class=\"Table\" style=\"background:white; border-collapse:collapse; border:solid black 1.0pt\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"background-color:white; border-color:black; height:24.75pt; width:33.0pt\">\r\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">NO</span></strong></span></span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"background-color:white; border-color:black; height:24.75pt; width:132.75pt\">\r\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">COLLECTION</span></strong></span></span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"background-color:white; border-color:black; height:24.75pt; width:109.15pt\">\r\n			<p style=\"text-align:center\"><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:12.0pt\">NO. OF TITLES</span></strong></span></span></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"background-color:white; border-color:black; height:24.75pt; width: