(44,NULL,'page_detail','International Office','<p style=\"margin-left:0cm; margin-right:0cm\"><strong><span style=\"color:black\">About &nbsp;</span></strong><strong><span style=\"color:black\">&nbsp;</span></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0cm; margin-right:0cm; text-align:justify\"><span style=\"color:black\">JGU&rsquo;s International Office (IO) was established in response to a new strategy which places international relations high on the University&rsquo;s list of priorities. This strategy recognizes that internationalization stretches across all the different university portfolios with the objective of developing an internationalization culture and institutional capacity through the transfer of know-how and good practice.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0cm; margin-right:0cm; text-align:justify\"><span style=\"color:black\">Strong international relations greatly assist the innovative reach of JGU and enable it to formulate meaningful research and exchange partnerships that provide access to resources and knowledge from the best institutions the world over.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0cm; margin-right:0cm; text-align:justify\"><span style=\"color:black\">The IO currently oversees and manages agreements and Memorandum of Understanding (MoU) and constantly seeks new international connections and partnerships.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0cm; margin-right:0cm; text-align:justify\"><span style=\"color:black\">The Office also carries out a number of activities which include the organization of quality conferences, workshops and seminars which complement its main role as a key driver of internationalization strategies for the University.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0cm; margin-right:0cm\"><strong><span style=\"color:black\">IO Functions</span></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ol start=\"1\" style=\"list-style-type:decimal\">\r\n	<li>Developing an internationalization culture through cooperative regional actions.</li>\r\n	<li>Providing appropriate knowledge, means, and methods to improve internationalization actions.</li>\r\n	<li>Creating a recognized regional network for good practice transfer.</li>\r\n	<li>Managing external projects for the University - Follow-up of all agreements and Memorandum of Understanding (MOU).</li>\r\n	<li>Maintaining the University&rsquo;s international contacts.</li>\r\n	<li>Supervising and counseling guest researchers and lecturers and international students who plan to carry out their studies or research at JGU.</li>\r\n	<li>Advising JGU students who wish to study, or join internship and leadership programs abroad.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0cm; margin-right:0cm\"><strong><span style=\"color:black\">Responsibilities</span></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul style=\"list-style-type:disc\">\r\n	<li>Coordination and implementation of all activities related to the establishment and maintenance of exchange agreements with universities abroad.</li>\r\n	<li>Providing administrative support for the exchange of students and faculty members with universities abroad.</li>\r\n	<li>Receiving exchange students from JGU partner institutions abroad and organizing their study programs.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0cm; margin-right:0cm\"><strong><span style=\"color:black\">Activities</span></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul style=\"list-style-type:disc\">\r\n	<li>Processing of applications of JGU students who wish to study abroad.</li>\r\n	<li>Processing applications of international students wishing to visit and register at JGU.</li>\r\n	<li>Providing academic advice, arranging summer school activities, and helping to arrange suitable accommodation for international students.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0cm; margin-right:0cm\"><strong><span style=\"color:black\">Services</span></strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ol start=\"1\" style=\"list-style-type:decimal\">\r\n	<li>Gathering and maintaining a database of all courses offered in the English language at JGU.</li>\r\n	<li>Providing information to JGU faculty and students about agreements with partner universities.</li>\r\n	<li>Creating brochures and guides for JGU use and external stakeholders about the University and its academic and non-academic services.</li>\r\n	<li>Maintaining a library of course catalogs, information brochures and other material from partner institutions.</li>\r\n	<li>Maintaining a searchable database of travel reports prepared by JGU students.</li>\r\n	<li>Maintaining up-to-date reference material on international study programs, including scholarships.</li>\r\n	<li>Establishing and developing an internationalization culture through cooperative regional actions.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<div>\r\n<ol style=\"list-style-type:undefined\">\r\n	<li><strong><span style=\"background-color:#f1f1f1\">Global Partnerships &amp; Agreements</span></strong></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</div>\r\n\r\n<p style=\"margin-left:0cm; margin-right:0cm\"><span style=\"color:black\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n\r\n<table cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"border-collapse:collapse; border:none\">\r\n	<tbody>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"vertical-align:top; width:150.15pt\">\r\n			<p style=\"margin-left:0cm; margin-right:0cm\"><strong><span style=\"color:black\">No.</span></strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-color:windowtext windowtext windowtext currentcolor; vertical-align:top; width:150.15pt\">\r\n			<p style=\"margin-left:0cm; margin-right:0cm\"><strong><span style=\"color:black\">Name of Partner Institution</span></strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n			<td style=\"border-color:windowtext windowtext windowtext currentcolor; vertical-align:top; width:150.2pt\">\r\n			<p style=\"margin-left:0cm; margin-right:0cm\"><strong><span style=\"color:black\">Duration of Validity</span></strong></p>\r\n			</td>\r\n		</tr>\r\n		<tr>\r\n			<td style=\"border-color:currentcolor windowtext windowtext; vertical-align:top; width:150.15pt\">\r\n			<p style=\"margin-left:0cm; margin-right:0cm\"><span style=\"