(116,NULL,'news_detail','JGU Ramadan Giving and Gratitude 2021','<p>Depok (21/05/2021) - A total of 279 participants consisting of orphans, high school students, female students and local residents have received compensation handed over by the Rector of Jakarta Global University (JGU).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The event took place solemnly at the JGU Auditorium, applying the COVID-19 Health Protocol standard. Participants are required to go through the registration process, check the temperature and must use a mask at the event.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&quot;This activity aims to remind all of us, that there are so many people around us that need to be helped and embraced. Hopefully this good activity can lighten the burden on the community a little because of the COVID-19 outbreak,&quot; said Prof. Dr. Eddy Yusuf, Chancellor of JGU</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This activity starts at 14.00 WIB - 18.00 WIB, attended by the Jakarta Global University Management, Lecturers, Staff and Employees. Also attended and enlivened by invited guests also by Ust. Abdillah Al-Haddad, SE., M. Si. who also gave Tazqiroh and Prayer on the sidelines of a series of events.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This compensation is expected to be useful and provide blessings to the recipient. The spirit of Ramadan is the spirit of doing good and sharing.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>#BlessingRamadan #JGUBerbagi #JGUSantunan #Giving #Gratitude #AyoKeJGU #BantuanSosial</p>\r\n\r\n<blockquote class=\"instagram-media\" data-instgrm-permalink=\"https://www.instagram.com/p/COAQYVRhj1U/?utm_source=ig_embed&amp;utm_campaign=loading\" data-instgrm-version=\"13\" style=\" background:#FFF; border:0; border-radius:3px; box-shadow:0 0 1px 0 rgba(0,0,0,0.5),0 1px 10px 0 rgba(0,0,0,0.15); margin: 1px; max-width:540px; min-width:326px; padding:0; width:99.375%; width:-webkit-calc(100% - 2px); width:calc(100% - 2px);\"><div style=\"padding:16px;\"> <a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/p/COAQYVRhj1U/?utm_source=ig_embed&amp;utm_campaign=loading\" style=\" background:#FFFFFF; lin