(132,NULL,'news_detail','JGU Global Mobility Program 2021 - Goes to Halic University','<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:9.0pt\"><span style=\"background-color:white\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto\"><span style=\"color:#011526\">Depok (23/09/2021) - Located at the Rectorate of the Jakarta Global University Main Campus, there was a release of students who will take part in the Global Mobility Program (GMP) Student Exchange, which was attended by JGU Chancellor Prof. Dr. Eddy Yusuf, M.Pharm., Deputy Chancellor I Bpk. Adhes Gamayel, Dean of the Faculty of Informatics and Computer Science, and Head of the Department of Informatics Engineering.</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:9.0pt\"><span style=\"background-color:white\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto\"><span style=\"color:#011526\">GMP is a student exchange program and distribution of international internships that are carried out for a certain period of time by Jakarta Global University and University and Industry Cooperation Partners. This time, the Global Mobility Program will be attended by Informatics Engineering Students, Ahmad Mukafi and Bima Rizky Ramadhan, who will study for 1 semester at Halic University, Turkey. In this program, students are expected to have the opportunity to open their horizons with international open-cultural experiences at related overseas campuses.</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size:11pt\"><span style=\"font-family:Calibri,sans-serif\"><span style=\"font-size:9.0pt\"><span style=\"background-color:white\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto\"><span style=\"color:#011526\">#GMP #GlobalMobilityProgram #JGU #HalicUniversity #StudentExchange</span></span></span></span></span></span></p>\r\n\r\n<blockquote class=\"instagram-media\" data-instgrm-captio